President Obama has designated Judge Patricia E. Campbell-Smith to be the Chief Judge of the U.S. Court of Federal Claims. Judge Campbell-Smith currently serves on the court and has a long and distinguished record of service. She previously served as a Special Master with the court and as Chief Special Master, presiding over litigation related to the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program. She has also worked in private practice focusing on environmental regulatory law, patent infringement litigation, and toxic tort litigation. Judge Campbell-Smith received her J.D. from Tulane Law School and her B.S. from Duke University.